            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Inside the code block, stop the loop after running its code block by updating <code>keepPlaying</code> to <code>false</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"var\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" keepPlaying = \" /><text value=\"true\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" keepPlaying {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"print\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Now Playing: Yummy&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" keepPlaying = \" /><text value=\"false\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"}\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"73\" endIndex=\"84\" /><option startIndex=\"85\" endIndex=\"86\" /><option startIndex=\"87\" endIndex=\"92\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Now Playing: Yummy\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>keepPlaying</code>, followed by <code>=</code>, and finally <code>false</code>.</p></body></html>"
